{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7934b5ff-bafe-418e-a118-6ee97eaa51ce","content":"Your code already uses `IFileSystem` from `System.IO.Abstractions`, which **is** the standard file system abstraction/wrapper for .NET. The `FileSystem` class is the concrete implementation, and you can inject it via DI:\n\n```csharp\nservices.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();\n```\n\nCould you clarify what you're looking for? For example:\n\n1. **A decorator** around `IFileSystem` that adds logging, error handling, or retry logic?\n2. **A simplified facade** exposing only the subset of file operations your app uses?\n3. **A test fake/mock** for unit testing?\n4. Something else?\n\nKnowing the goal will help me generate exactly what you need.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47a0e6ba-d911-4740-831a-328c23a5ef5c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a simple .NET project using `System.IO.Abstractions` with `IFileSystem`. They want me to generate a file system wrapper. \n\nBut wait - `System.IO.Abstractions` already IS a file system abstraction/wrapper. The `IFileSystem` interface is the abstraction, and `FileSystem` is the concrete implementation that wraps the real file system.\n\nLet me think about what the user might actually want. They might want:\n1. A wrapper class that wraps `IFileSystem` with additional functionality\n2. A concrete implementation of some custom interface\n3. A test double/mock helper\n\nActually, re-reading the request: \"My code already uses IFileSystem from System.IO.Abstractions everywhere. Can you generate a file system wrapper for me?\"\n\n\nI think they're looking for a custom wrapper or facade that sits on top of `IFileSystem` - maybe something that adds logging, error handling, or simplifies the API for their specific use case. But I should clarify what they're actually trying to accomplish, since `IFileSystem` is already serving as the abstraction layer they need.","outputTokens":551,"requestId":"4C2B:E616E:CD17C7